HEADWORD: Squad
<hw>Squad</hw> <pr>(skw⟦ocr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>escouade</ets>, fr. Sp. <ets>escuadra</ets>, or It.
<ets>squadra</ets>, (assumed) LL. <ets>exquadrare</ets> to square; L.
<ets>ex + quadra</ets> a square. See <er>Square</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A small party of men assembled for drill,
inspection, or other purposes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, any small party.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squad</ent>⟦br⟧

